    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey my realtor mentioned i need to deal with an escrow account for the house closing in toronto. i've never done this before, can u explain what escrow actually is and why we use it during the closing process?",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
    {
      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "Escrow, in the context of a Toronto house closing, is essentially a temporary holding place for funds and documents, managed by a neutral third party—usually a lawyer or a real estate professional. Think of it like a highly secure, temporary holding pen for your money and the paperwork, preventing any one party from getting the upper hand before all the conditions are met. It's crucial because it ensures that when the deal is done, both you and the seller get exactly what you are supposed to get, without any last-minute shenanigans. This process is vital for keeping the entire transaction smooth, safe, and compliant with the laws of the land.",
      "source": "target",
